    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@tris203, can you do a rebase? Currently, the pull diagnostics for the different identifiers are not working as intended because they are overwriting each other. This should not be a problem in master because `handle_diagnostics` uses namespaces per identifier, so that should fix the issue.\r\n\r\nI actually think there might be a bug in master at the moment because workspace diagnostics use namespaces but text document diagnostics do not. As a result, the workspace diagnostics are not getting overwritten by the text document diagnostics. This PR should fix that issue.\r\n\r\nAlso, another question: should previous resultIds be per diagnostic identifier? When looking at the resultIds being sent from the server (I'm testing with Roslyn), I would assume so. For example, a resultId might be `PublicDocumentPullDiagnosticsHandler(category: DocumentAnalyzerSemantic):3`, where DocumentAnalyzerSemantic is an identifier we sent.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure @MariaSolOs @mfussenegger, do either of you maybe know?",
            "created_at": "2026-03-16T15:41:59Z",
